Uses of Package
core

  • Packages that use core 
    Package Description
    app
    Contains the Application class which is the foundation class for the entire application.
    core
    Core classes necessary for the base operations involved in Mirror including FileSet (defines properties and methods for manipulating the settings for a Mirror operation) as well the FileOps class (provides standard mirroring operations).
    test
    Contains unit tests for key operational classes.
    ui
    Contains user interface classes.
  • Classes in core used by app 
    Class and Description
    FileSet
    Contains a complete specification for a backup operation.
  • Classes in core used by core 
    Class and Description
    FileOpsMessageHandler
    Defines required methods for any class that wants to receive Progress updates from the FileOps operation as it proceeds.
    FileSet
    Contains a complete specification for a backup operation.
    Progress
    The Progress class represents a point-in-time progress indication of the copy operation.
  • Classes in core used by test 
    Class and Description
    FileOpsMessageHandler
    Defines required methods for any class that wants to receive Progress updates from the FileOps operation as it proceeds.
    Progress
    The Progress class represents a point-in-time progress indication of the copy operation.
  • Classes in core used by ui 
    Class and Description
    FileOps
    The FileOps class defines the operation and behavior of the entire backup process.
    FileOpsMessageHandler
    Defines required methods for any class that wants to receive Progress updates from the FileOps operation as it proceeds.
    FileSet
